    "posts": [
      {
        "id": 3998503,
        "name": "Guillermo M e n a",
        "username": "Guillermo_M",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/guillermo_m/{size}/3751_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-02-02T02:15:47.624Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=4277732&amp;iNote=10296920\"><b>2019 Jean Javillier Volnay</b></a> - France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Volnay (2/1/2023)<br>\nTasted over two days with no significant changes. This was my first red from this producer. <br><br>On first impression it struck me as overripe and over extracted, especially for Volnay. However this could be an artifact of the vintage, as I explain below.<br><br>Spicy pine almost to the point of charcoal dominates the nose. The mouth is a supple, silky wave of plum with some notions of red fruits and spices. Lingering red fruits sustain the long finish. I\u2019m not sure, but I suspect this was fully destemmed and in my opinion might have benefited from some whole clusters.<br><br>William Kelley called Alain Javillier\u2019s reds sumptuous, supple and elegant. Based on only this bottle I will agree with the first two. <br><br>Since William says Alain told him he would only let him taste wines made with massal selections (not clones), and William did not rate this wine, another possibility is that this wine is made from clones which we know is not Alain\u2019s preference. But this is only speculation.<br><br>My impression regarding over-extraction led me to look at ABV which is listed as 14%; the same as his 2019 Clos des Ch\u00eanes, which I also own. If you\u2019ve never read my reviews, I\u2019ve used the word hate for a 14.9% Pinot Noir, so if you don\u2019t care so much about ripeness, then you might enjoy this more than I did.<br><br>Alain\u2019s 2020 version of this wine lists ABV at a comparatively refreshing 13.5% and his 2020 Clos des Ch\u00eanes comes in a full point below the 2019 at 13%. I have bottles of both. So, for my usual taste, there are signs of much better days on the horizon (and in my cellar). I still have high hopes.<br><br>Standard cork. Not great QPR at $39 this vintage. (Par for the course in Burgundy.) <b>(88 points)</b><br><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/d/2/d2d266b565563133adef9f6314a81db1d7895fb4.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/d2d266b565563133adef9f6314a81db1d7895fb4\" title=\"3c087177-3fb3-4f01-b319-7315e48741da.jpg\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/2/d2d266b565563133adef9f6314a81db1d7895fb4_2_375x500.jpeg\" data-base62-sha1=\"u513bbIan7q39sMVJVWtxXvPzXC\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/2/d2d266b565563133adef9f6314a81db1d7895fb4_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/2/d2d266b565563133adef9f6314a81db1d7895fb4_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/2/d2d266b565563133adef9f6314a81db1d7895fb4_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"837063\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">3c087177-3fb3-4f01-b319-7315e48741da.jpg</span><span class=\"informations\">768\u00d71024 113 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>",
