      {
        "id": 4019645,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-02-28T19:28:51.965Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Could indeed just be clones that good a bit too mature in the vintage. Could also be in an awkward phase. You\u2019re correct that I\u2019ve never tasted this particular cuv\u00e9e, but given that Alain doesn\u2019t use press wine and there\u2019s no funny business regarding extraction, I don\u2019t think the winemaking was the problem.</p>",
